# Use Tailwind, Avoid CSS

Use Tailwind utility classes for styling. Avoid writing custom CSS or SCSS.

## Guidelines

- Use Tailwind classes directly in components (e.g. `class="flex gap-4 p-4 rounded-lg"`)
- Do not create new `.css` or `.scss` files for component styles
- Use `@apply` sparingly and only when a pattern repeats; prefer inline Tailwind classes
- For layout, typography, spacing, colors: use Tailwind utilities

## Examples

```svelte
<!-- ❌ BAD - custom CSS -->
<style>
  .card { padding: 1rem; border-radius: 0.5rem; }
</style>
<div class="card">...</div>

<!-- ✅ GOOD - Tailwind -->
<div class="p-4 rounded-lg">...</div>
```
